column1: #Text=Subscriptions received for the week ending December 24th, 1862 : Mansion House Committee 2000 0 0 Ditto for Christmas Dinners .. 550 0 0 Ditto for the Overlookers’ Special Fund .. 300 Q 0 Ditto Christmas Dinners for Overlookers.. 25 0 0 Miss Mellor (Ist donation) 10 0 0 Messrs.
#Text=Donations in money, or gifts of clothes, or materials for clothing and bedding will be thankfully accepted by the Chairman or either of the Honorary Secretaries.
#Text=THE BOARD OF GOVERNORS of the DISTRICT INFIRMARY, Ashtoo-anderLyne, are prepared to receive TENDERS for the supply of the following articles : Butter percwt.
#Text=House Coal and Burgy mixed.. per ton.
#Text=Samples of the groceries, bread, flour, and meal to be sent to the District Infirmary, with sealed tenders, addressed to H.
#Text=Sec., not later than 12 o’clock on Wednesday, the 31st day of December, 1862.
#Text=The Board of Governors do not bind themselves to accept the lowest tenders.
#Text=Forms of tender to be had on application.
